The paper focuses on learning compact binary representations for multimedia data, specifically images and texts, using convolutional neural networks and multilabel classification. The proposed method also involves cross-view hashing and view alignment, which are common techniques in computer vision and multimedia analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning and information retrieval techniques, which suggest possible sub-categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions image annotation/tagging, which is a task related to natural language processing and text analysis, suggesting a possible sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
